freQ is a Jabber bot, written by Burdakov Daniel <kreved@kreved.org>

To run bot, you need have installed:

       * python25-2.5.1           - http://python.org/
       * py25-twistedCore-2.5.0   - http://twistedmatrix.com/
       * py25-twistedWords-0.5.0  - http://twistedmatrix.com/
       * py25-twistedWeb-0.7.0    - http://twistedmatrix.com/

Optionally:

       * sqlite3-3.4.1            - http://sqlite.org/
       * py25-sqlite3-2.5.1_1     - http://python.org/

   (run "python ./tools/depends.py" to check if you have installed all dependencies)


1) You can install FreQ on your system using command:

   make install (or gmake install)

   * it works correctly on FreeBSD, otherwise you should edit Makefile manually 


2) or, if you can't (or don't want) install bot, you can run it directly...

   copy freq.conf.example to freq.conf and edit it..

   Start bot with command like this:

      python2.5 start.py /path/to/freq.conf
